description:
We manufacture cold-finished long products in Specialty Stainless Steels.

Our facilities include end-to-end manufacturing starting from Hot Rolling of Billets (& Ingots) up to Heat Treatment & Cold Finishing of a wide variety of product forms including Rounds, Squares, Hexagons, Angles, Flat bars & custom Profiles. 

We produce materials in a wide-ranging steel grades like Austenitic, Ferritic, Martensitic, Heat Resisting, Duplex & 17-4ph steels in various heat treatment conditions including Quenched Tempered, Annealed, Solution Annealed etc.

description:
This is the official Facebook page of BMW Motorrad - Navnit Motors,Mumbai — the page for enthusiasts, fans and riders of BMW motorcycles. It is packed with news, information and entertaining features related to BMW Motorrad India. Our mission is to bring the JOY of BMW Motorrad to Facebook. 

But this page is not just about us — it’s also about you! Send us pictures of your BMW bike, tell us what you love most about riding and let us know what we can do for you. 

Although we’re sure that you’re already well-versed in netiquette we would still like to remind everyone to keep the tone friendly and respectful. 

Comments, opinions and images posted by fans on this page do not necessarily reflect the opinions of BMW Motorrad India.

description:
Blue Ashva Capital is an investment firm based out of Singapore and India, backing sustainable and profitable businesses which are solving real challenges in areas such as Food & Agri, Energy & Environment, Health & Wellness and Money & Finance.

It aims to nurture businesses by bringing capital, technology and market linkages together.

Blue Ashva also runs a deep-tech incubator called Blue Ashva Labs, which focuses on taking technologies from lab to market. Some of the focus areas include green hydrogen, pharma APIs, biotechnology and battery recycling.

description: Boundless is a full-stack E-Commerce platform for the F&B industry with a digital first portfolio beverage brands. From their taste palette to how Millennials and GenZ discover, engage and consume beverages, everything is going through a rapid evolution and Boundless Brands is building their line of beverages products and their full-stack E-Commerce platform for the F&B industry to capture this paradigm shift. Boundless plans to launch array of beverages drinks in the summer of 2023 to be distributed through its own E-Commerce site and app supplemented with Q

description: Operating out of Central India, Buildkraft works on engaging the complexity of spaces, embracing architecture’s role as a catalyst and designing infrastructure for the future. For this reason, the Buildkraft creed incorporates a research oriented approach that results in innovative architectural and engineering designs with longevity. Thoroughly informed research, innovation, quality and efficiency are not only imperative but also pivotal to the firm's design philosophy. With a conscious understanding that architecture and infrastructure operate within a layered context of political, developmental, environmental and social structures, Buildkraft seeks to elevate the human condition through design of the the built environment.

description:
Casambi is changing the way people and businesses light their surroundings.

Since 2011, Casambi has been developing wireless lighting control systems based on Bluetooth Low Energy. Today, we are the market leader. 

A dynamic user experience, excellent reliability and unparalleled performance are already enjoyed via hundreds of third-party Casambi ecosystem providers. Our technology can be integrated into any lighting installation – from individual lighting fixture controls to industrial-scale solutions with cloud-based remote control, monitoring and data logging.
 
Casambi has a growing sales and support network across Europe, North America and Asia. We are always interested in meeting new partners to join us on this journey.

description:
Delta Lighting Design was established in Dubai in 1998 and in London in 2014 with one simple mission: to offer the highest standard of creative lighting design and client service. We have achieved this by recruiting top design talent from all over the world, having strong project ownership, providing effective and efficient project communication and response times and providing excellent ground support.

We feel a strong ownership to our projects and are protective of the end result, giving each project it’s due time and creating a discernable identity for each tower, hotel, museum, city plan, public building or retail center that we design.

Featuring a simple drag-and-drop user interface and a vast range of templates ranging from presentations, documents, websites, social media graphics, posters, apparel to videos, plus a huge library of fonts, stock photography, illustrations, video footage, and audio clips, anyone can take an idea and create something beautiful on Canva on any device, from anywhere in the world.

Since our launch in 2013, we’ve had the crazy big goal of making design accessible to everyone. We were founded on the belief that people shouldn't need to understand complex software to unlock their creativity. We’re leveling the playing field and democratizing access

description:
We started out in 2011 as India’s first communications consultancy run by architects, for architects. For our founder Tanya Khanna, the idea was straightforward: to craft compelling narratives about the built environment. Through the last decade, we have donned a few more hats, stepped into new territories, and grown from a one-woman mission to a 50+ team across 5+ cities. Today, we generate dialogue and enable outreach – in many ways, for many people. And while the scale and scope of our operations may have expanded, our mission remains the same – to democratise architecture.

Today, businesses operate within an increasingly competitive market, and cultivating a unique identity and voice is crucial for growth. This is where we come in. We

description:
Octopus Data Inc. is a software company specialized in collecting data from both static and dynamic websites. 

Octoparse is a visual & automatic web data extraction software which simulates human operation to interact with web pages. You can use our point-&-click UI to easily bulk extract web data from web pages (including those using Ajax, JS, and etc.) and there are various export formats of your choice like CSV, Excel, HTML, TXT, and database (MySQL, SQL Server, and Oracle). 

Our cloud service supports extracting and storing a large volume of data in the cloud for large-scale extraction needs.

description:
Khaitan & Co is one of India's oldest and recognised full service law firms.

Built on foundations of integrity, simplicity, dedication and professionalism, the Firm has expanded its presence in India from Kolkata (1911) to New Delhi (1970) to Bangalore (1994) to Mumbai (2001) to Chennai and Singapore (2021) and Pune and Ahmedabad (2024). The Firm takes pride in its steady growth and celebrated its centenary year in 2011 (11 November 2011).

The Firm has a strength of more than 1200 + fee earners including 300 + leaders across its offices. In addition to the fee-earners, Khaitan & Co and has over 1000 employees working for it.

description: Founded in 2019, Lentra is enabling banks in democratising digital lending through its SaaS platform. It empowers banks (& NBFCs) to create custom loan products and enhance customer experiences, through its API-driven modular architecture. Currently, Lentra's digital lending platform serves over 50 banks, has processed over $20 billion worth of loan applications, with 2 million loans being processed every month. Lentra supports its customers in expanding their reach, reducing non-performing assets, optimising operational efficiencies, and using Pay-as-you-go pricing for their growth. Lentra is backed by investors like BVP, Citi, HDFC, MUFG, SIG & Vy. To read more, please visit: https://Lentra.ai/

description:
MANTION—European sliding system specialist since 1920.  

Since 1920, MANTION has designed, manufactured and distributed sliding systems for the construction industry—such as door, gate and shutter fittings—from its outfit in Besançon, France. It caters for the residential market through its building trade and industrial partners. Present on five continents, MANTION products are used throughout the world by leading construction companies. 

Today, MANTION employs 200 people in seven countries. With more than 4,500 product references, a special product offering and a constant R&D effort, MANTION always has, or can tailor-fit, the right solution. 

Discover our product range at www.mantion.com

description:
Pareto Capital derives its name from the well-known Pareto Principle named after Italian economist Vilfredo Pareto. Pareto’s 80/20 rule states that in any given situation 80% impact is derived from 20% factors.  We at Pareto follow this principle in how we engage, execute and deliver results for our clients. We hand-hold our clients to help them identify precisely that 20% that generate 80% impact. Our focus is on identifying the elements that will have the most profound impact on the end goal and will yield the greatest results.

An increasing number of companies need external partners who provide a helicopter picture of the where the company is, where it needs to go and what resources it will need to transition from one point to another e

description:
VENZOWOOD:  Quality backed by aesthetics
With a consistent penchant for quality, Venzowood offers veneers that adapt to the vision of the architect. Venzowood believes that a veneer is not just a commodity; the brand treats each veneer as a legacy of nature that calls for an acquired proficiency for curation. Sourced from local suppliers Worldwide, specially in Europe, North America and South America, the veneers go through numerous filtration processes to showcase a uniform grain and variation. The veneers are then classified as per different aesthetic values namely – grains, colour and texture to heighten the features of wood in a sturdy thickness ranging from 0.5mm to 2.4 mm so that the products are durable to use.

The Journey so far:
A

Since Alan Turing's groundbreaking ideas in 1936, envisioning a machine capable of automatic mathematical operations, and John von Neumann's seminal proposal of the first computer architecture in 1945, we have witnessed the incredible capabilities of computers over the past 80 years. From the early stages of computing to the current era of 12-24 pipelined stages CPU architectures and billions of lines of code, our journey has been transformative.

description:
Athmer - the art of sealing. Globally sought after, and

hidden to the eye, they are nevertheless absolutely essential: Efficient and reliable door seals provide security, comfort and energy efficiency for buildings. 

Athmer is at the cutting edge when it comes to developing and producing sophisticated automatic door seals. Sealing systems from the traditional German company are in great demand. And not without good reason! Athmer sealing solutions offer high flexibility, sophisticated technology and functions and are sustainable and efficient. 

And since more and more people live and work in buildings, Athmer has also taken safety to extremes: with finger protection systems that make door injuries a thing of the past.
